307// CRC_32_Table (Little Endian bitstream, )
308// The CRC in use is the IEEE-CRC-32 algorithm as used in the ISO 3309 standard and in section 8.1.1.6.2 of ITU-T recommendation V.42, with initial value of 0xFFFFFFFF. The CRC value MUST be computed on a little endian bitstream and MUST use little endian storage.
309// A CRC is computed like this:
310// Init: int32u CRC32 ^= 0;
311// for each data byte do
312// CRC32=(CRC32>>8) ^ Mk_CRC32_Table[(CRC32&0xFF)^*Buffer_Current++];
313// End: CRC32 ^= 0;

432//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
433const char* Mk_OriginalSourceMedium_From_Source_ID (const Ztring &Value)
434{
435 if (Value.size()==6 && Value[0] == __T('0') && Value[1] == __T('0'))
436 return "Blu-ray";
437 if (Value.size()==6 && Value[0] == __T('0') && Value[1] == __T('1'))
438 return "DVD-Video";
439 return "";
440}
441
442//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
443Ztring Mk_ID_From_Source_ID (const Ztring &Value)
444{
445 if (Value.size()==6 && Value[0] == __T('0') && Value[1] == __T('0'))
446 {
447 // Blu-ray
448 int16u ValueI=0;
449 for (size_t Pos=2; Pos<Value.size(); Pos++)
450 {
451 ValueI*=16;
452 if (Value[Pos]>=__T('0') && Value[Pos]<=__T('9'))
453 ValueI+=Value[Pos]-__T('0');
454 else if (Value[Pos]>=__T('A') && Value[Pos]<=__T('F'))
455 ValueI+=10+Value[Pos]-__T('A');
456 else if (Value[Pos]>=__T('a') && Value[Pos]<=__T('f'))
457 ValueI+=10+Value[Pos]-__T('a');
458 else
459 return Value;
460 }
461 return Ztring::ToZtring(ValueI);
462 }
463
464 if (Value.size()==6 && Value[0] == __T('0') && Value[1] == __T('1'))
465 {
466 // DVD-Video
467 int16u ValueI=0;
468 for (size_t Pos=2; Pos<Value.size(); Pos++)
469 {
470 ValueI*=16;
471 if (Value[Pos]>=__T('0') && Value[Pos]<=__T('9'))
472 ValueI+=Value[Pos]-__T('0');
473 else if (Value[Pos]>=__T('A') && Value[Pos]<=__T('F'))
474 ValueI+=10+Value[Pos]-__T('A');
475 else if (Value[Pos]>=__T('a') && Value[Pos]<=__T('f'))
476 ValueI+=10+Value[Pos]-__T('a');
477 else
478 return Value;
479 }
480 int8u ID1 = ValueI&0xFF;
481 int8u ID2 = 0;
482 ValueI-=ID1;
483 if (ValueI)
484 ID2=ValueI>>8;
485
486 return Ztring::ToZtring(ID1) + (ID2?(__T('-') + Ztring::ToZtring(ID2)):Ztring());
487 }
488
489 return Value;
490}
491
492//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
493Ztring Mk_ID_String_From_Source_ID (const Ztring &Value)
494{
495 if (Value.size()==6 && Value[0] == __T('0') && Value[1] == __T('0'))
496 {
497 // Blu-ray
498 int16u ValueI=0;
499 for (size_t Pos=2; Pos<Value.size(); Pos++)
500 {
501 ValueI*=16;
502 if (Value[Pos]>=__T('0') && Value[Pos]<=__T('9'))
503 ValueI+=Value[Pos]-__T('0');
504 else if (Value[Pos]>=__T('A') && Value[Pos]<=__T('F'))
505 ValueI+=10+Value[Pos]-__T('A');
506 else if (Value[Pos]>=__T('a') && Value[Pos]<=__T('f'))
507 ValueI+=10+Value[Pos]-__T('a');
508 else
509 return Value;
510 }
511
512 return Ztring::ToZtring(ValueI) + __T(" (0x") + Ztring::ToZtring(ValueI, 16) + __T(")");
513 }
514
515 if (Value.size()==6 && Value[0] == __T('0') && Value[1] == __T('1'))
516 {
517 // DVD-Video
518 int16u ValueI=0;
519 for (size_t Pos=2; Pos<Value.size(); Pos++)
520 {
521 ValueI*=16;
522 if (Value[Pos]>=__T('0') && Value[Pos]<=__T('9'))
523 ValueI+=Value[Pos]-__T('0');
524 else if (Value[Pos]>=__T('A') && Value[Pos]<=__T('F'))
525 ValueI+=10+Value[Pos]-__T('A');
526 else if (Value[Pos]>=__T('a') && Value[Pos]<=__T('f'))
527 ValueI+=10+Value[Pos]-__T('a');
528 else
529 return Value;
530 }
531 int8u ID1 = ValueI&0xFF;
532 int8u ID2 = 0;
533 ValueI-=ID1;
534 if (ValueI)
535 ID2=ValueI>>8;
536
537 return Ztring::ToZtring(ID1) + __T(" (0x") + Ztring::ToZtring(ID1, 16) + __T(")") + (ID2?(__T('-') + Ztring::ToZtring(ID2) + __T(" (0x") + Ztring::ToZtring(ID2, 16) + __T(")")):Ztring());
538 }
539
540 return Value;
541}

598//***************************************************************************
599// Streams management
600//***************************************************************************
601
602//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
603void File_Mk::Streams_Finish()
604{
605 if (Duration!=0 && TimecodeScale!=0)
606 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Duration, Duration*int64u_float64(TimecodeScale)/1000000.0, 0);
607
608 //Tags (General)
609 for (tags::iterator Item=Segment_Tags_Tag_Items.begin(); Item!=Segment_Tags_Tag_Items.end(); ++Item)
610 if (!Item->first || Item->first == (int64u)-1)
611 {
612 for (tagspertrack::iterator Tag=Item->second.begin(); Tag!=Item->second.end(); ++Tag)
613 if ((Tag->first!=__T("Encoded_Library") || Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Encoded_Library").empty()) // Prioritize Info block over tags
614 && (Tag->first!=__T("Encoded_Date") || Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Encoded_Date").empty())
615 && (Tag->first!=__T("Title") || Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Title").empty()))
616 Fill(Stream_General, 0, Tag->first.To_UTF8().c_str(), Tag->second);
617 }
618
619 for (std::map<int64u, stream>::iterator Temp=Stream.begin(); Temp!=Stream.end(); ++Temp)
620 {
621 StreamKind_Last=Temp->second.StreamKind;
622 StreamPos_Last=Temp->second.StreamPos;
623
624 //Tags (per track)
625 if (Temp->second.TrackUID && Temp->second.TrackUID!=(int64u)-1)
626 {
627 tags::iterator Item=Segment_Tags_Tag_Items.find(Temp->second.TrackUID);
628 if (Item != Segment_Tags_Tag_Items.end())
629 {
630 for (tagspertrack::iterator Tag=Item->second.begin(); Tag!=Item->second.end(); ++Tag)
631 if ((Tag->first!=__T("Language") || Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Language").empty())) // Prioritize Tracks block over tags
632 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Tag->first.To_UTF8().c_str(), Tag->second);
633 }
634 }
635
636 //Tags
637 //Ztring Duration_Temp;
638 float64 FrameRate_FromTags = 0.0;
639 Ztring TagsList=Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "_STATISTICS_TAGS");
640 if (TagsList.size())
641 {
642 bool Tags_Verified=false;
643 {
644 Ztring Happ = Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, "Encoded_Application");
645 Ztring Hutc = Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, "Encoded_Date");
646 Ztring App = Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "_STATISTICS_WRITING_APP");
647 Ztring Utc = Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "_STATISTICS_WRITING_DATE_UTC");
648 Clear(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "_STATISTICS_WRITING_APP");
649 Clear(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "_STATISTICS_WRITING_DATE_UTC");
650 Clear(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "_STATISTICS_TAGS");
651 Hutc.FindAndReplace(__T("UTC "), Ztring());
652 if (App==Happ && Utc==Hutc) Tags_Verified=true;
653 else Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Statistics Tags Issue", App + __T(' ') + Utc + __T(" / ") + Happ + __T(' ') + Hutc);
654 }
655 Ztring TempTag;
656
657 float64 Statistics_Duration=0;
658 float64 Statistics_FrameCount=0;
659 for (Ztring::iterator Back = TagsList.begin();;++Back)
660 {
661 if ((Back == TagsList.end()) || (*Back == ' ') || (*Back == '\0'))
662 {
663 if (TempTag.size())
664 {
665 Ztring TagValue = Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, TempTag.To_Local().c_str());
666 if (TagValue.size())
667 {
668 Clear(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, TempTag.To_Local().c_str());
669 bool Set=false;
670 if (TempTag==__T("BPS"))
671 {
672 if (Tags_Verified)
673 { Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_BitRate), TagValue, true); Set=true; }
674 else
675 TempTag="BitRate";
676 }
677 else if (TempTag==__T("DURATION"))
678 {
679 if (Tags_Verified)
680 {
681 ZtringList Parts;
682 Parts.Separator_Set(0, ":");
683 Parts.Write(TagValue);
684 Statistics_Duration=0;
685 if (Parts.size()>=1)
686 Statistics_Duration += Parts[0].To_float64()*60*60;
687 if (Parts.size()>=2)
688 Statistics_Duration += Parts[1].To_float64()*60;
689 int8u Rounding=0; //Default is rounding to milliseconds, TODO: rounding to less than millisecond when "Duration" field is changed to seconds.
690 if (Parts.size()>=3)
691 {
692 Statistics_Duration += Parts[2].To_float64();
693 if (Parts[2].size()>6) //More than milliseconds
694 Rounding=Parts[2].size()-6;
695 }
696 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Duration), Statistics_Duration*1000, Rounding, true);
697 Set=true;
698 //Duration_Temp = TagValue;
699 }
700 if (!Set) TempTag="Duration";
701 }
702 else if (TempTag==__T("NUMBER_OF_FRAMES"))
703 {
704 if (Tags_Verified)
705 {
706 Statistics_FrameCount=TagValue.To_float64();
707 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_FrameCount), TagValue, true);
708 if (StreamKind_Last==Stream_Text)
709 {
710 const Ztring &Format=Retrieve(Stream_Text, StreamPos_Last, "Format");
711 if (Format.find(__T("608"))==string::npos && Format.find(__T("708"))==string::npos)
712 Fill(Stream_Text, StreamPos_Last, Text_ElementCount, TagValue, true); // if not 608 or 708, this is used to be also the count of elements
713 }
714 Set=true;
715 }
716 else
717 TempTag="FrameCount";
718 }
719 else if (TempTag==__T("NUMBER_OF_BYTES"))
720 {
721 if (Tags_Verified)
722 {
723 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_StreamSize), TagValue, true);
724 Set=true;
725 }
726 else
727 TempTag="StreamSize";
728 }
729 else if (TempTag==__T("NUMBER_OF_BYTES_UNCOMPRESSED"))
730 {
731 if (Tags_Verified)
732 {
733 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "StreamSize_Demuxed", TagValue, true);
734 Set=true;
735 }
736 else
737 TempTag="Stream Size (Uncompressed)";
738 }
739 else if (TempTag==__T("SOURCE_ID"))
740 {
741 if (Tags_Verified)
742 {
743 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "OriginalSourceMedium_ID", Mk_ID_From_Source_ID(TagValue), true);
744 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "OriginalSourceMedium_ID/String", Mk_ID_String_From_Source_ID(TagValue), true);
745 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_OriginalSourceMedium, Mk_OriginalSourceMedium_From_Source_ID(TagValue), Unlimited, true, true);
746 Set=true;
747 }
748 else
749 TempTag="OriginalSourceMedium_ID";
750 }
751 if (!Set)
752 {
753 TempTag.insert(0, __T("FromStats_"));
754 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, TempTag.To_Local().c_str(), TagValue.To_Local().c_str());
755 }
756 }
757 if (Back == TagsList.end())
758 break;
759 TempTag.clear();
760 }
761 }
762 else
763 TempTag+=*Back;
764 }
765 if (Statistics_Duration && Statistics_FrameCount)
766 {
767 FrameRate_FromTags = Statistics_FrameCount/Statistics_Duration;
768 if (float64_int64s(FrameRate_FromTags) - FrameRate_FromTags*1.001 > -0.0001
769 && float64_int64s(FrameRate_FromTags) - FrameRate_FromTags*1.001 < +0.0001)
770 {
771 // Checking 1.001 frame rates, Statistics_Duration is has often only a 1 ms precision so we test between -1ms and +1ms
772 float64 Duration_1001 = Statistics_FrameCount / float64_int64s(FrameRate_FromTags) * 1.001000;
773 float64 Duration_1000 = Statistics_FrameCount / float64_int64s(FrameRate_FromTags) * 1.001001;
774 bool CanBe1001 = false;
775 bool CanBe1000 = false;
776 if (abs((Duration_1000 - Duration_1001) * 10000) >= 15)
777 {
778 Ztring DurationS; DurationS.From_Number(Statistics_Duration, 3);
779 Ztring DurationS_1001; DurationS_1001.From_Number(Duration_1001, 3);
780 Ztring DurationS_1000; DurationS_1000.From_Number(Duration_1000, 3);
781
782 CanBe1001=DurationS==DurationS_1001?true:false;
783 CanBe1000=DurationS==DurationS_1000?true:false;
784 if (CanBe1001 && !CanBe1000)
785 FrameRate_FromTags = float64_int64s(FrameRate_FromTags) / 1.001;
786 if (CanBe1000 && !CanBe1001)
787 FrameRate_FromTags = float64_int64s(FrameRate_FromTags) / 1.001001;
788 }
789
790 // Duration from tags not reliable, checking TrackDefaultDuration
791 if (CanBe1000 == CanBe1001)
792 {
793 float64 Duration_Default=((float64)1000000000)/Temp->second.TrackDefaultDuration;
794 if (float64_int64s(Duration_Default) - Duration_Default*1.001000 > -0.000002
795 && float64_int64s(Duration_Default) - Duration_Default*1.001000 < +0.000002) // Detection of precise 1.001 (e.g. 24000/1001) taking into account precision of 32-bit float
796 {
797 FrameRate_FromTags = float64_int64s(FrameRate_FromTags) / 1.001;
798 }
799 if (float64_int64s(Duration_Default) - Duration_Default*1.001001 > -0.000002
800 && float64_int64s(Duration_Default) - Duration_Default*1.001001 < +0.000002) // Detection of rounded 1.001 (e.g. 23976/1000) taking into account precision of 32-bit float
801 {
802 FrameRate_FromTags = float64_int64s(FrameRate_FromTags) / 1.001001;
803 }
804 }
805 }
806
807 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_FrameRate), FrameRate_FromTags, 3, true);
808 }
809 }
810
811 if (Temp->second.DisplayAspectRatio!=0)
812 {
813 //Corrections
814 if (Temp->second.DisplayAspectRatio>=1.777 && Temp->second.DisplayAspectRatio<=1.778)
815 Temp->second.DisplayAspectRatio=((float32)16)/9;
816 if (Temp->second.DisplayAspectRatio>=1.333 && Temp->second.DisplayAspectRatio<=1.334)
817 Temp->second.DisplayAspectRatio=((float32)4)/3;
818 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_DisplayAspectRatio, Temp->second.DisplayAspectRatio, 3, true);
819 int64u Width=Retrieve(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Width).To_int64u();
820 int64u Height=Retrieve(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Height).To_int64u();
821 if (Width)
822 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_PixelAspectRatio, Temp->second.DisplayAspectRatio*Height/Width, 3, true);
823 }
824
825 if (Temp->second.Parser)
826 {
827 Fill(Temp->second.Parser);
828 if (Config->ParseSpeed<=1.0)
829 Temp->second.Parser->Open_Buffer_Unsynch();
830 }
831
832 //Video specific
833 if (StreamKind_Last==Stream_Video)
834 {
835 //FrameRate
836 bool IsVfr=false;
837 if (Temp->second.Segment_Cluster_BlockGroup_BlockDuration_Counts.size()>2)
838 IsVfr=true;
839 else if (Temp->second.TimeCodes.size()>1)
840 {
841 //Trying to detect VFR
842 std::vector<int64s> FrameRate_Between;
843 std::sort(Temp->second.TimeCodes.begin(), Temp->second.TimeCodes.end()); //This is PTS, no DTS --> Some frames are out of order
844 size_t FramesToAdd=0;
845 for (size_t Pos=1; Pos<Temp->second.TimeCodes.size(); Pos++)
846 {
847 int64u Duration=Temp->second.TimeCodes[Pos]-Temp->second.TimeCodes[Pos-1];
848 if (Duration)
849 FrameRate_Between.push_back(Duration);
850 else
851 FramesToAdd++;
852 }
853 if (FrameRate_Between.size()>=60+32) //Minimal 1 seconds (@60 fps)
854 FrameRate_Between.resize(FrameRate_Between.size()-16); //We remove the last ones, because this is PTS, no DTS --> Some frames are out of order
855 std::sort(FrameRate_Between.begin(), FrameRate_Between.end());
856 if (FrameRate_Between.size()>2)
857 {
858 //Looking for 3 consecutive same values, in order to remove some missing frames from stats
859 size_t i=FrameRate_Between.size()-1;
860 int64s Previous = FrameRate_Between[i];
861 do
862 {
863 i--;
864 if (FrameRate_Between[i]==Previous && FrameRate_Between[i-1]==Previous)
865 break;
866 Previous=FrameRate_Between[i];
867 }
868 while (i>2);
869 if (i>FrameRate_Between.size()/2)
870 FrameRate_Between.resize(i+2);
871 }
872
873 if (FrameRate_Between.size()>=40)
874 FrameRate_Between.resize(FrameRate_Between.size()-FrameRate_Between.size()/10); //We remove the last ones, in order to ignore skipped frames (bug of the muxer?)
875 else if (FrameRate_Between.size()>=7)
876 FrameRate_Between.resize(FrameRate_Between.size()-4); //We remove the last ones, in order to ignore skipped frames (bug of the muxer?)
877 if (FrameRate_Between.size()>2
878 && FrameRate_Between[0]*0.9<FrameRate_Between[FrameRate_Between.size()-1]
879 && FrameRate_Between[0]*1.1>FrameRate_Between[FrameRate_Between.size()-1]
880 && TimecodeScale)
881 {
882 float Time=0;
883 for (size_t i=0; i<FrameRate_Between.size(); i++)
884 Time += FrameRate_Between[i];
885 Time /= FrameRate_Between.size();
886
887 if (Temp->second.TrackDefaultDuration && Time>=Temp->second.TrackDefaultDuration/TimecodeScale*0.95 && Time<=Temp->second.TrackDefaultDuration/TimecodeScale*1.05)
888 Time=(float)Temp->second.TrackDefaultDuration/TimecodeScale; //TrackDefaultDuration is maybe more precise than the time code
889
890 if (Time)
891 {
892 float32 FrameRate_FromCluster=1000000000/Time/TimecodeScale;
893 if (Temp->second.Parser)
894 {
895 float32 FrameRate_FromParser=Temp->second.Parser->Retrieve(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameRate).To_float32();
896 if (FrameRate_FromParser
897 && FrameRate_FromParser*2>FrameRate_FromCluster*0.9
898 && FrameRate_FromParser*2<FrameRate_FromCluster*1.1) //TODO: awfull method to detect interlaced content with one field per block
899 FrameRate_FromCluster/=2;
900 }
901 if (FrameRate_FromTags)
902 {
903 if (FrameRate_FromCluster < FrameRate_FromTags - (FrameRate_FromTags*(TimecodeScale*0.0000000010021)) || FrameRate_FromCluster > FrameRate_FromTags + (FrameRate_FromTags*(TimecodeScale*0.0000000010021)))
904 IsVfr=true;
905 }
906 else
907 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameRate, FrameRate_FromCluster);
908 }
909 }
910 else if (FrameRate_Between.size()>2)
911 IsVfr=true;
912 }
913
914 else if (Temp->second.TrackDefaultDuration)
915 {
916 float32 FrameRate_FromCluster=1000000000/(float32)Temp->second.TrackDefaultDuration;
917 if (Retrieve(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameRate).empty())
918 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameRate, FrameRate_FromCluster);
919 }
920
921 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameRate_Mode, IsVfr?"VFR":"CFR");
922 }
923
924 if (Temp->second.Parser)
925 {
926 //Delay
927 if (Temp->second.TimeCode_Start!=(int64u)-1 && TimecodeScale)
928 {
929 //From TimeCode
930 float64 Delay=Temp->second.TimeCode_Start*int64u_float64(TimecodeScale)/1000000.0;
931
932 //From stream format
933 if (StreamKind_Last==Stream_Audio && Count_Get(Stream_Video)==1 && Temp->second.Parser->Count_Get(Stream_General)>0)
934 {
935 if (Temp->second.Parser->Buffer_TotalBytes_FirstSynched==0)
936 ;
937 else if (Temp->second.AvgBytesPerSec!=0)
938 Delay+=((float64)Temp->second.Parser->Buffer_TotalBytes_FirstSynched)*1000/Temp->second.AvgBytesPerSec;
939 else
940 {
941 int64u BitRate = Temp->second.Parser->Retrieve(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_BitRate).To_int64u();
942 if (BitRate == 0)
943 BitRate = Temp->second.Parser->Retrieve(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_BitRate_Nominal).To_int64u();
944 if (BitRate)
945 Delay += ((float64)Temp->second.Parser->Buffer_TotalBytes_FirstSynched) * 1000 / BitRate;
946 }
947 }
948
949 //Filling
950 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Delay), Delay, 0, true);
951 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Delay_Source), "Container");
952 }
953
954 Ztring Codec_Temp=Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Codec)); //We want to keep the 4CC;
955 //if (Duration_Temp.empty()) Duration_Temp=Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, Temp->second.StreamPos, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Duration)); //Duration from stream is sometimes false
956 //else Duration_Temp.clear();
957
958 Finish(Temp->second.Parser);
959 Merge(*Temp->second.Parser, StreamKind_Last, 0, StreamPos_Last);
960 //if (!Duration_Temp.empty()) Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Duration), Duration_Temp, true);
961 if (Temp->second.StreamKind==Stream_Video && !Codec_Temp.empty())
962 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Codec), Codec_Temp, true);
963
964 //Special case: AAC
965 if (StreamKind_Last==Stream_Audio
966 && (Retrieve(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Format)==__T("AAC")
967 || Retrieve(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Format)==__T("MPEG Audio")
968 || Retrieve(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Format)==__T("Vorbis")))
969 Clear(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_BitDepth); //Resolution is not valid for AAC / MPEG Audio / Vorbis
970
971 //Special case: 5.1
972 if (StreamKind_Last==Stream_Audio
973 && (Retrieve(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Format)==__T("AC-3")
974 || Retrieve(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Format)==__T("E-AC-3")
975 || Retrieve(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Format)==__T("DTS"))
976 && Retrieve(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Channel_s__Original)==__T("6")
977 && Retrieve(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Channel_s_)==__T("5"))
978 {
979 Clear(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Channel_s__Original);
980 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Channel_s_, 6, 10, true); //Some muxers do not count LFE in the channel count, let's say it is normal
981 }
982
983 //VFR
984 if (Retrieve(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameRate_Mode)==__T("VFR") && Retrieve(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameRate_Original).empty())
985 {
986 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameRate_Original, Retrieve(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameRate));
987 Clear(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameRate);
988 }
989
990 //Crop
991 if (Temp->second.PixelCropLeft || Temp->second.PixelCropRight)
992 {
993 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Width_Original, Retrieve(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Width), true);
994 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Width, Retrieve(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Width).To_int64u()-Temp->second.PixelCropLeft-Temp->second.PixelCropRight, 10, true);
995 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Width_Offset, Temp->second.PixelCropLeft, 10, true);
996 }
997 if (Temp->second.PixelCropTop || Temp->second.PixelCropBottom)
998 {
999 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Height_Original, Retrieve(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Height), true);
1000 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Height, Retrieve(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Height).To_int64u()-Temp->second.PixelCropTop-Temp->second.PixelCropBottom, 10, true);
1001 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Height_Offset, Temp->second.PixelCropTop, 10, true);
1002 }
1003 }
1004
1005 if (Temp->second.FrameRate!=0 && Retrieve(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameRate).empty())
1006 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameRate, Temp->second.FrameRate, 3);
1007
1008 //Flags
1009 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Default", Temp->second.Default?"Yes":"No");
1010 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Forced", Temp->second.Forced?"Yes":"No");
1011 }
1012
1013 //Chapters
1014 if (TimecodeScale)
1015 {
1016 for (EditionEntries_Pos=0; EditionEntries_Pos<EditionEntries.size(); EditionEntries_Pos++)
1017 {
1018 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Menu);
1019 Fill(Stream_Menu, StreamPos_Last, Menu_Chapters_Pos_Begin, Count_Get(Stream_Menu, StreamPos_Last), 10, true);
1020 for (ChapterAtoms_Pos=0; ChapterAtoms_Pos<EditionEntries[EditionEntries_Pos].ChapterAtoms.size(); ChapterAtoms_Pos++)
1021 {
1022 if (EditionEntries[EditionEntries_Pos].ChapterAtoms[ChapterAtoms_Pos].ChapterTimeStart!=(int64u)-1)
1023 {
1024 Ztring Text;
1025 for (ChapterDisplays_Pos=0; ChapterDisplays_Pos<EditionEntries[EditionEntries_Pos].ChapterAtoms[ChapterAtoms_Pos].ChapterDisplays.size(); ChapterDisplays_Pos++)
1026 {
1027 Ztring PerLanguage;
1028 if (!EditionEntries[EditionEntries_Pos].ChapterAtoms[ChapterAtoms_Pos].ChapterDisplays[ChapterDisplays_Pos].ChapLanguage.empty())
1029 PerLanguage=MediaInfoLib::Config.Iso639_1_Get(EditionEntries[EditionEntries_Pos].ChapterAtoms[ChapterAtoms_Pos].ChapterDisplays[ChapterDisplays_Pos].ChapLanguage)+__T(':');
1030 PerLanguage+=EditionEntries[EditionEntries_Pos].ChapterAtoms[ChapterAtoms_Pos].ChapterDisplays[ChapterDisplays_Pos].ChapString;
1031 Text+=PerLanguage+__T(" - ");
1032 }
1033 if (Text.size())
1034 Text.resize(Text.size()-3);
1035 Fill(Stream_Menu, StreamPos_Last, Ztring().Duration_From_Milliseconds(EditionEntries[EditionEntries_Pos].ChapterAtoms[ChapterAtoms_Pos].ChapterTimeStart/1000000).To_UTF8().c_str(), Text);
1036 }
1037 }
1038 Fill(Stream_Menu, StreamPos_Last, Menu_Chapters_Pos_End, Count_Get(Stream_Menu, StreamPos_Last), 10, true);
1039 }
1040 }
1041
1042 //Purge what is not needed anymore
1043 if (!File_Name.empty()) //Only if this is not a buffer, with buffer we can have more data
1044 Stream.clear();
1045}

1047//***************************************************************************
1048// Buffer
1049//***************************************************************************
1050
1051//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1052void File_Mk::Header_Parse()
1053{
1054 //Test of zero padding
1055 int8u Null;
1056 Peek_B1(Null);
1057 if (Null<=InvalidByteMax)
1058 {
1059 if (Buffer_Offset_Temp==0)
1060 Buffer_Offset_Temp=Buffer_Offset+1;
1061
1062 while (Buffer_Offset_Temp<Buffer_Size)
1063 {
1064 if (Buffer[Buffer_Offset_Temp]>InvalidByteMax)
1065 break;
1066 Buffer_Offset_Temp++;
1067 }
1068 if (Buffer_Offset_Temp>=Buffer_Size)
1069 {
1070 Element_WaitForMoreData();
1071 return;
1072 }
1073
1074 Header_Fill_Code((int32u)-1); //Should be (int64u)-1 but Borland C++ does not like this
1075 Header_Fill_Size(Buffer_Offset_Temp-Buffer_Offset);
1076 Buffer_Offset_Temp=0;
1077
1078 return;
1079 }
1080
1081 //Parsing
1082 int64u Name, Size;
1083 bool NameIsValid=true;
1084 if (Element_Offset+1<Element_Size)
1085 {
1086 int8u NamePeek;
1087 Peek_B1(NamePeek);
1088 if (NamePeek<0x10)
1089 {
1090 Skip_B1( "Invalid");
1091 #if MEDIAINFO_TRACE
1092 Element_Level--;
1093 Element_Info("NOK");
1094 Element_Level++;
1095 #endif //MEDIAINFO_TRACE
1096 NameIsValid=false;
1097
1098 Header_Fill_Code(0, "Junk");
1099 Header_Fill_Size(1);
1100 }
1101 }
1102 if (NameIsValid)
1103 {
1104 Get_EB (Name, "Name");
1105 Get_EB (Size, "Size");
1106
1107 //Filling
1108 Header_Fill_Code(Name, Ztring().From_Number(Name, 16));
1109 Header_Fill_Size(Element_Offset+Size);
1110 }
1111
1112 if ((Name==Elements::Segment_Cluster_BlockGroup_Block || Name==Elements::Segment_Cluster_SimpleBlock) && Buffer_Offset+Element_Offset+Size>Buffer_Size && File_Buffer_Size_Hint_Pointer)
1113 {
1114 int64u Buffer_Size_Target = (size_t)(Buffer_Offset + Element_Offset + Size - Buffer_Size + Element_Offset); //+Element_Offset for next packet header
1115
1116 if (Buffer_Size_Target<128 * 1024)
1117 Buffer_Size_Target = 128 * 1024;
1118 (*File_Buffer_Size_Hint_Pointer) = (size_t)Buffer_Size_Target;
1119
1120 Element_WaitForMoreData();
1121 return;
1122 }
1123
1124 //Incoherencies
1125 if (Element_Level<=2 && File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_Offset+Size>File_Size)
1126 Fill(Stream_General, 0, "IsTruncated", "Yes");
1127}

1435 ATOM_END_MK
1436 ATOM(Segment_Tracks_TrackEntry_TrackOverlay)
1437 LIST(Segment_Tracks_TrackEntry_TrackTranslate)
1438 ATOM_BEGIN
1439 ATOM(Segment_Tracks_TrackEntry_TrackTranslate_Codec)
1440 ATOM(Segment_Tracks_TrackEntry_TrackTranslate_EditionUID)
1441 ATOM(Segment_Tracks_TrackEntry_TrackTranslate_TrackID)
1442 ATOM_END_MK
1443 ATOM_END_MK
1444 ATOM_END_MK
1445 ATOM_END_MK
1446 DATA_END
1447
1448 if (!CRC32Compute.empty())
1449 CRC32_Check();
1450}

1464//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1465void File_Mk::CRC32()
1466{
1467 Element_Name("CRC-32");
1468
1469 //Parsing
1470 if (Element_Size!=4)
1471 UInteger_Info(); //Something is wrong, 4-byte integer is expected
1472 else
1473 {
1474 if (CRC32Compute.empty())
1475 Fill(Stream_General, 0, "ErrorDetectionType", Element_Level==3?"Per level 1":"Custom", Unlimited, true, true);
1476
1477 if (CRC32Compute.size()<Element_Level)
1478 CRC32Compute.resize(Element_Level);
1479
1480 Get_L4(CRC32Compute[Element_Level-1].Expected, "Value");
1481
1482 {
1483 Param_Info1(__T("Not tested ")+Ztring::ToZtring(Element_Level-1)+__T(' ')+Ztring::ToZtring(CRC32Compute[Element_Level-1].Expected));
1484 CRC32Compute[Element_Level-1].Computed=0xFFFFFFFF;
1485 CRC32Compute[Element_Level-1].Pos = File_Offset + Buffer_Offset;
1486 CRC32Compute[Element_Level-1].From = File_Offset + Buffer_Offset + Element_Size;
1487 CRC32Compute[Element_Level-1].UpTo = File_Offset + Buffer_Offset + Element_TotalSize_Get(1);
1488 }
1489 }
1490}

1984//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1985void File_Mk::Segment_Cluster()
1986{
1987 Element_Name("Cluster");
1988
1989 //For each stream
1990 std::map<int64u, stream>::iterator Temp=Stream.begin();
1991 if (!Segment_Cluster_Count)
1992 {
1993 Stream_Count=0;
1994 while (Temp!=Stream.end())
1995 {
1996 if (Temp->second.Parser)
1997 Temp->second.Searching_Payload=true;
1998 if (Temp->second.StreamKind==Stream_Video || Temp->second.StreamKind==Stream_Audio)
1999 Temp->second.Searching_TimeStamp_Start=true;
2000 if (Temp->second.StreamKind==Stream_Video)
2001 Temp->second.Searching_TimeStamps=true;
2002 if (Temp->second.Searching_Payload
2003 || Temp->second.Searching_TimeStamp_Start
2004 || Temp->second.Searching_TimeStamps)
2005 Stream_Count++;
2006
2007 //Specific cases
2008 #ifdef MEDIAINFO_AAC_YES
2009 if (Retrieve(Temp->second.StreamKind, Temp->second.StreamPos, Audio_CodecID).find(__T("A_AAC/"))==0)
2010 ((File_Aac*)Stream[Temp->first].Parser)->Mode=File_Aac::Mode_raw_data_block; //In case AudioSpecificConfig is not present
2011 #endif //MEDIAINFO_AAC_YES
2012
2013 ++Temp;
2014 }
2015
2016 //We must parse moov?
2017 if (Stream_Count==0)
2018 {
2019 //Jumping
2020 std::sort(Segment_Seeks.begin(), Segment_Seeks.end());
2021 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Segment_Seeks.size(); Pos++)
2022 if (Segment_Seeks[Pos]>File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_Size)
2023 {
2024 JumpTo(Segment_Seeks[Pos]);
2025 break;
2026 }
2027 if (File_GoTo==(int64u)-1)
2028 JumpTo(Segment_Offset_End);
2029 return;
2030 }
2031 }
2032 Segment_Cluster_Count++;
2033 Segment_Cluster_TimeCode_Value=0; //Default
2034}
2035
2036//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2037void File_Mk::Segment_Cluster_BlockGroup()
2038{
2039 Element_Name("BlockGroup");
2040
2041 Segment_Cluster_BlockGroup_BlockDuration_Value=(int64u)-1;
2042 Segment_Cluster_BlockGroup_BlockDuration_TrackNumber=(int64u)-1;
2043}
2044
2045//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2046void File_Mk::Segment_Cluster_BlockGroup_Block()
2047{
2048 Element_Name(Element_Level==3?"SimpleBlock":"Block");
2049
2050 //Parsing
2051 int64u TrackNumber;
2052 Get_EB (TrackNumber, "TrackNumber");
2053
2054 //Finished?
2055 Stream[TrackNumber].PacketCount++;
2056 if (Stream[TrackNumber].Searching_Payload || Stream[TrackNumber].Searching_TimeStamps || Stream[TrackNumber].Searching_TimeStamp_Start)
2057 {
2058 //Parsing
2059 int16u TimeCodeU;
2060 Get_B2 (TimeCodeU, "TimeCode"); // Should be signed, but we don't have signed integer reader
2061 int16s TimeCode = (int16s)TimeCodeU;
2062 Element_Info1(TimeCodeU);
2063
2064 FILLING_BEGIN();
2065 if (Segment_Cluster_TimeCode_Value+TimeCode<Stream[TrackNumber].TimeCode_Start) //Does not work well: Stream[TrackNumber].Searching_TimeStamp_Start)
2066 {
2067 FILLING_BEGIN();
2068 Stream[TrackNumber].TimeCode_Start=Segment_Cluster_TimeCode_Value+TimeCode;
2069 //Stream[TrackNumber].Searching_TimeStamp_Start=false;
2070 FILLING_END();
2071 }
2072 if (Stream[TrackNumber].Searching_TimeStamps)
2073 {
2074 Stream[TrackNumber].TimeCodes.push_back(Segment_Cluster_TimeCode_Value+TimeCode);
2075 if (Stream[TrackNumber].TimeCodes.size()>128)
2076 Stream[TrackNumber].Searching_TimeStamps=false;
2077 }
2078
2079 if (Segment_Cluster_BlockGroup_BlockDuration_Value!=(int64u)-1)
2080 {
2081 Stream[TrackNumber].Segment_Cluster_BlockGroup_BlockDuration_Counts[Segment_Cluster_BlockGroup_BlockDuration_Value]++;
2082 Segment_Cluster_BlockGroup_BlockDuration_Value=(int64u)-1;
2083 }
2084 FILLING_END();
2085
2086 if (Stream[TrackNumber].Searching_Payload)
2087 {
2088 std::vector<int64u> Laces;
2089 int32u Lacing;
2090 Element_Begin1("Flags");
2091 BS_Begin();
2092 Skip_BS(1, "KeyFrame");
2093 Skip_BS(3, "Reserved");
2094 Skip_BS(1, "Invisible");
2095 Get_BS (2, Lacing, "Lacing");
2096 Skip_BS(1, "Discardable");
2097 BS_End();
2098 Element_End0();
2099 if (Lacing>0)
2100 {
2101 Element_Begin1("Lacing");
2102 int8u FrameCountMinus1;
2103 Get_B1(FrameCountMinus1, "Frame count minus 1");
2104 switch (Lacing)
2105 {
2106 case 1 : //Xiph lacing
2107 {
2108 int64u Element_Offset_Virtual=0;
2109 for (int8u Pos=0; Pos<FrameCountMinus1; Pos++)
2110 {
2111 int32u Size=0;
2112 int8u Size8;
2113 do
2114 {
2115 Get_B1 (Size8, "Size");
2116 Size+=Size8;
2117 }
2118 while (Size8==0xFF);
2119 Param_Info1(Size);
2120 Element_Offset_Virtual+=Size;
2121 Laces.push_back(Size);
2122 }
2123 Laces.push_back(Element_Size-Element_Offset-Element_Offset_Virtual); //last lace
2124 }
2125 break;
2126 case 2 : //Fixed-size lacing - No more data
2127 {
2128 int64u Size=(Element_Size-Element_Offset)/(FrameCountMinus1+1);
2129 Laces.resize(FrameCountMinus1+1, Size);
2130 }
2131 break;
2132 case 3 : //EBML lacing
2133 {
2134 int64u Element_Offset_Virtual=0, Size;
2135 Get_EB (Size, "Size");
2136 Laces.push_back(Size);
2137 Element_Offset_Virtual+=Size;
2138 for (int8u Pos=1; Pos<FrameCountMinus1; Pos++)
2139 {
2140 int64s Diff;
2141 Get_ES (Diff, "Difference");
2142 Size+=Diff; Param_Info1(Size);
2143 Element_Offset_Virtual+=Size;
2144 Laces.push_back(Size);
2145 }
2146 Laces.push_back(Element_Size-Element_Offset-Element_Offset_Virtual); Param_Info1(Size); //last lace
2147 }
2148 break;
2149 default : ; //Should never be here
2150 }
2151 Element_End0();
2152 }
2153 else
2154 Laces.push_back(Element_Size-Element_Offset);
2155
2156 FILLING_BEGIN();
2157 //Parsing
2158 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Laces.size(); Pos++)
2159 {
2160 //Content compression
2161 if (Stream[TrackNumber].ContentCompAlgo!=(int32u)-1 && Stream[TrackNumber].ContentCompAlgo!=3)
2162 Stream[TrackNumber].Searching_Payload=false; //Unsupported
2163
2164 //Integrity test
2165 if (Element_Offset+Laces[Pos]>Element_Size)
2166 Stream[TrackNumber].Searching_Payload=false; //There is a problem
2167
2168 if (Stream[TrackNumber].Searching_Payload)
2169 {
2170 Element_Begin1("Data");
2171 Element_Parser(Stream[TrackNumber].Parser->ParserName.c_str());
2172
2173 Element_Code=TrackNumber;
2174
2175 //Content compression
2176 if (Stream[TrackNumber].ContentCompAlgo==3) //Header Stripping
2177 {
2178 Element_Offset-=(size_t)Stream[TrackNumber].ContentCompSettings_Buffer_Size; //This is an extra array, not in the stream
2179 Open_Buffer_Continue(Stream[TrackNumber].Parser, Stream[TrackNumber].ContentCompSettings_Buffer, (size_t)Stream[TrackNumber].ContentCompSettings_Buffer_Size);
2180 Element_Offset+=(size_t)Stream[TrackNumber].ContentCompSettings_Buffer_Size;
2181 Demux(Stream[TrackNumber].ContentCompSettings_Buffer, (size_t)Stream[TrackNumber].ContentCompSettings_Buffer_Size, ContentType_MainStream);
2182 }
2183
2184 //Parsing
2185 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
2186 int8u Demux_Level_old=Demux_Level;
2187 if (Stream[TrackNumber].Parser && Stream[TrackNumber].Parser->Demux_Level==2)
2188 Demux_Level=4;
2189 Demux(Buffer+Buffer_Offset+(size_t)Element_Offset, (size_t)(Element_Size-Element_Offset), ContentType_MainStream);
2190 Demux_Level=Demux_Level_old;
2191 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
2192 Open_Buffer_Continue(Stream[TrackNumber].Parser, (size_t)Laces[Pos]);
2193 if (Stream[TrackNumber].Parser->Status[IsFinished]
2194 || (Stream[TrackNumber].PacketCount>=300 && MediaInfoLib::Config.ParseSpeed_Get()<1))
2195 Stream[TrackNumber].Searching_Payload=false;
2196
2197 Element_End0();
2198 }
2199 else
2200 Skip_XX(Laces[Pos], "Data");
2201 }
2202
2203 //Positionning
2204 Element_Offset=Element_Size;
2205 FILLING_END();
2206 }
2207 else
2208 {
2209 Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset, "Data");
2210 }
2211
2212 if (!Stream[TrackNumber].Searching_Payload && !Stream[TrackNumber].Searching_TimeStamps && !Stream[TrackNumber].Searching_TimeStamp_Start)
2213 Stream_Count--;
2214 }
2215 else
2216 {
2217 Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset, "Data");
2218 }
2219
2220 //Filling
2221 Frame_Count++;
2222 if (!Status[IsFilled] && ((Frame_Count>6 && (Stream_Count==0 ||Config->ParseSpeed==0.0)) || Frame_Count>512*Stream.size()))
2223 {
2224 Fill();
2225 if (MediaInfoLib::Config.ParseSpeed_Get()<1)
2226 {
2227 //Jumping
2228 std::sort(Segment_Seeks.begin(), Segment_Seeks.end());
2229 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Segment_Seeks.size(); Pos++)
2230 if (Segment_Seeks[Pos]>File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_Size)
2231 {
2232 JumpTo(Segment_Seeks[Pos]);
2233 break;
2234 }
2235 if (File_GoTo==(int64u)-1)
2236 JumpTo(Segment_Offset_End);
2237 }
2238 }
2239
2240 Element_Show(); //For debug
2241}

2784//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2785void File_Mk::Segment_Tags_Tag_SimpleTag_TagString()
2786{
2787 Element_Name("TagString");
2788
2789 //Parsing
2790 Ztring TagString;
2791 TagString=UTF8_Get();
2792
2793 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames.empty())
2794 return;
2795 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("AERMS_OF_USE")) Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]=__T("TermsOfUse"); //Typo in the source file
2796 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("BITSPS")) return; //Useless
2797 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("COMPATIBLE_BRANDS")) return; //QuickTime techinical info, useless
2798 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("CONTENT_TYPE")) Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]=__T("ContentType");
2799 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("COPYRIGHT")) Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]=__T("Copyright");
2800 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("CREATION_TIME")) {Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]=__T("Encoded_Date"); TagString.insert(0, __T("UTC "));}
2801 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("DATE_DIGITIZED")) {Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]=__T("Mastered_Date"); TagString.insert(0, __T("UTC "));}
2802 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("DATE_RELEASE")) Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]=__T("Released_Date");
2803 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("DATE_RELEASED")) Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]=__T("Released_Date");
2804 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("DESCRIPTION")) Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]=__T("Description");
2805 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("ENCODED_BY")) Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]=__T("EncodedBy");
2806 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("ENCODER")) Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]=__T("Encoded_Library");
2807 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("FPS")) return; //Useless
2808 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("LANGUAGE")) Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]=__T("Language");
2809 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("MAJOR_BRAND")) return; //QuickTime techinical info, useless
2810 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("MINOR_VERSION")) return; //QuickTime techinical info, useless
2811 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("PART_NUMBER")) Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]=__T("Track/Position");
2812 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("ORIGINAL_MEDIA_TYPE")) Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]=__T("OriginalSourceForm");
2813 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("SAMPLE") && Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames.size()==2 && Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[1]==__T("PART_NUMBER")) return; //Useless
2814 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("SAMPLE") && Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames.size()==2 && Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[1]==__T("TITLE")) {Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames.resize(1); Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]=__T("Title_More");}
2815 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("STEREO_MODE")) return; //Useless
2816 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("TERMS_OF_USE")) Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]=__T("TermsOfUse");
2817 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("TITLE")) Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]=__T("Title");
2818 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]==__T("TOTAL_PARTS")) Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[0]=__T("Track/Position_Total");
2819 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames.size(); Pos++)
2820 {
2821 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[Pos]==__T("BARCODE")) Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[Pos]=__T("BarCode");
2822 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[Pos]==__T("COMMENT")) Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[Pos]=__T("Comment");
2823 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[Pos]==__T("ORIGINAL")) Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[Pos]=__T("Original");
2824 if (Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[Pos]==__T("URL")) Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[Pos]=__T("Url");
2825 }
2826
2827 Ztring TagName;
2828 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames.size(); Pos++)
2829 {
2830 TagName+=Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames[Pos];
2831 if (Pos+1<Segment_Tag_SimpleTag_TagNames.size())
2832 TagName+=__T('/');
2833 }
2834
2835 Segment_Tags_Tag_Items[Segment_Tags_Tag_Targets_TagTrackUID_Value][TagName]=TagString;
2836}

2914//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2915void File_Mk::Segment_Tracks_TrackEntry()
2916{

2920 return; //First element has the priority
2921
2922 //Clearing

3122//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
3123void File_Mk::Segment_Tracks_TrackEntry_CodecPrivate()
3124{
3125 Element_Name("CodecPrivate");
3126
3127 if (Segment_Info_Count>1)
3128 {
3129 Skip_XX(Element_Size, "Data (not parsed)");
3130 return; //First element has the priority
3131 }
3132
3133 if (TrackNumber==(int64u)-1 || TrackType==(int64u)-1 || Retrieve(Stream[TrackNumber].StreamKind, Stream[TrackNumber].StreamPos, "CodecID").empty())
3134 {
3135 //Codec not already known, saving CodecPrivate
3136 if (CodecPrivate)
3137 delete[] CodecPrivate; //CodecPrivate=NULL.
3138 CodecPrivate_Size=(size_t)Element_Size;
3139 CodecPrivate=new int8u[CodecPrivate_Size];
3140 std::memcpy(CodecPrivate, Buffer+Buffer_Offset, CodecPrivate_Size);
3141 return;
3142 }
3143
3144 Segment_Tracks_TrackEntry_CodecPrivate__Parse();
3145}
3146
3147//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
3148void File_Mk::Segment_Tracks_TrackEntry_CodecPrivate__Parse()
3149{
3150 //Creating the parser
3151 if (Stream[TrackNumber].Parser==NULL)
3152 {
3153 if (Stream[TrackNumber].StreamKind==Stream_Audio && Retrieve(Stream_Audio, Stream[TrackNumber].StreamPos, Audio_CodecID)==__T("A_MS/ACM"))
3154 Segment_Tracks_TrackEntry_CodecPrivate_auds();
3155 else if (Stream[TrackNumber].StreamKind==Stream_Video && Retrieve(Stream_Video, Stream[TrackNumber].StreamPos, Video_CodecID)==__T("V_MS/VFW/FOURCC"))
3156 Segment_Tracks_TrackEntry_CodecPrivate_vids();
3157 else if (Element_Size>0)
3158 Skip_XX(Element_Size, "Unknown");
3159 return;
3160 }
3161
3162 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
3163 switch (Config->Demux_InitData_Get())
3164 {
3165 case 0 : //In demux event
3166 {
3167 Demux_Level=2; //Container
3168 int64u Element_Code_Old=Element_Code;
3169 Element_Code=TrackNumber;
3170 Demux(Buffer+Buffer_Offset, (size_t)Element_Size, ContentType_Header);
3171 Element_Code=Element_Code_Old;
3172 }
3173 break;
3174 case 1 : //In field
3175 {
3176 std::string Data_Raw((const char*)(Buffer+Buffer_Offset), (size_t)Element_Size);
3177 std::string Data_Base64(Base64::encode(Data_Raw));
3178 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Demux_InitBytes", Data_Base64);
3179 (*Stream_More)[StreamKind_Last][StreamPos_Last](Ztring().From_Local("Demux_InitBytes"), Info_Options)=__T("N NT");
3180 }
3181 break;
3182 default : ;
3183 }
3184 #endif // MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
3185
3186 //Parsing
3187 Open_Buffer_Continue(Stream[TrackNumber].Parser);
3188
3189 //Filling
3190 if (Stream[TrackNumber].Parser->Status[IsFinished]) //Can be finnished here...
3191 {
3192 Stream[TrackNumber].Searching_Payload=false;
3193 Stream_Count--;
3194 }
3195
3196 //In case of problem
3197 Element_Show();
3198}

3200//--------------------------------------------------------------------------
3201void File_Mk::Segment_Tracks_TrackEntry_CodecPrivate_auds()
3202{
3203 Element_Info1("Copy of auds");
3204
3205 //Parsing
3206 int32u SamplesPerSec;
3207 int16u FormatTag, Channels, BitsPerSample;
3208 Get_L2 (FormatTag, "FormatTag");
3209 Get_L2 (Channels, "Channels");
3210 Get_L4 (SamplesPerSec, "SamplesPerSec");
3211 Get_L4 (AvgBytesPerSec, "AvgBytesPerSec");
3212 Skip_L2( "BlockAlign");
3213 Get_L2 (BitsPerSample, "BitsPerSample");
3214
3215 //Filling
3216 FILLING_BEGIN();
3217 InfoCodecID_Format_Type=InfoCodecID_Format_Riff;
3218 CodecID.From_Number(FormatTag, 16);
3219 CodecID_Fill(CodecID, Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff);
3220 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Codec, CodecID, true); //May be replaced by codec parser
3221 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Codec_CC, CodecID);
3222 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Channel_s_, Channels!=5?Channels:6, 10, true);
3223 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_SamplingRate, SamplesPerSec, 10, true);
3224 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_BitRate, AvgBytesPerSec*8, 10, true);
3225 if (BitsPerSample)
3226 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_BitDepth, BitsPerSample);
3227
3228 CodecID_Manage();
3229 if (TrackNumber!=(int64u)-1)
3230 Stream[TrackNumber].AvgBytesPerSec=AvgBytesPerSec;
3231 FILLING_END();
3232
3233 //Options
3234 if (Element_Offset+2>Element_Size)
3235 return; //No options
3236
3237 //Parsing
3238 int16u Option_Size;
3239 Get_L2 (Option_Size, "cbSize");
3240
3241 //Filling
3242 if (Option_Size>0)
3243 {
3244 if (FormatTag==0xFFFE) //Extensible Wave
3245 Segment_Tracks_TrackEntry_CodecPrivate_auds_ExtensibleWave();
3246 else Skip_XX(Option_Size, "Unknown");
3247 }
3248}

3250//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
3251void File_Mk::Segment_Tracks_TrackEntry_CodecPrivate_auds_ExtensibleWave()
3252{
3253 //Parsing
3254 int128u SubFormat;
3255 int32u ChannelMask;
3256 Skip_L2( "ValidBitsPerSample / SamplesPerBlock");
3257 Get_L4 (ChannelMask, "ChannelMask");
3258 Get_GUID(SubFormat, "SubFormat");
3259
3260 FILLING_BEGIN();
3261 if ((SubFormat.hi&0xFFFFFFFFFFFF0000LL)==0x0010000000000000LL && SubFormat.lo==0x800000AA00389B71LL)
3262 {
3263 CodecID_Fill(Ztring().From_Number((int16u)SubFormat.hi, 16), Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff);
3264 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_CodecID, Ztring().From_GUID(SubFormat), true);
3265 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Codec, MediaInfoLib::Config.Codec_Get(Ztring().From_Number((int16u)SubFormat.hi, 16)), true);
3266
3267 //Creating the parser
3268 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_PCM_YES)
3269 if (MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(Stream_Audio, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Ztring().From_Number((int16u)SubFormat.hi, 16))==__T("PCM"))
3270 {
3271 //Creating the parser
3272 File_Pcm MI;
3273 MI.Frame_Count_Valid=0;
3274 MI.Codec=Ztring().From_Number((int16u)SubFormat.hi, 16);
3275
3276 //Parsing
3277 Open_Buffer_Init(&MI);
3278 Open_Buffer_Continue(&MI, 0);
3279
3280 //Filling
3281 Finish(&MI);
3282 Merge(MI, StreamKind_Last, 0, StreamPos_Last);
3283 }
3284 #endif
3285 }
3286 else
3287 {
3288 CodecID_Fill(Ztring().From_GUID(SubFormat), Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff);
3289 }
3290 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_ChannelPositions, ExtensibleWave_ChannelMask(ChannelMask));
3291 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_ChannelPositions_String2, ExtensibleWave_ChannelMask2(ChannelMask));
3292 FILLING_END();
3293}

3295//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
3296void File_Mk::Segment_Tracks_TrackEntry_CodecPrivate_vids()
3297{
3298 Element_Info1("Copy of vids");
3299
3300 //Parsing
3301 int32u Width, Height, Compression;
3302 int16u Resolution;
3303 Skip_L4( "Size");
3304 Get_L4 (Width, "Width");
3305 Get_L4 (Height, "Height");
3306 Skip_L2( "Planes");
3307 Get_L2 (Resolution, "BitCount");
3308 Get_C4 (Compression, "Compression");
3309 Skip_L4( "SizeImage");
3310 Skip_L4( "XPelsPerMeter");
3311 Skip_L4( "YPelsPerMeter");
3312 Skip_L4( "ClrUsed");
3313 Skip_L4( "ClrImportant");
3314
3315 FILLING_BEGIN();
3316 Ztring Codec;
3317 if (((Compression&0x000000FF)>=0x00000020 && (Compression&0x000000FF)<=0x0000007E
3318 && (Compression&0x0000FF00)>=0x00002000 && (Compression&0x0000FF00)<=0x00007E00
3319 && (Compression&0x00FF0000)>=0x00200000 && (Compression&0x00FF0000)<=0x007E0000
3320 && (Compression&0xFF000000)>=0x20000000 && (Compression&0xFF000000)<=0x7E000000)
3321 || Compression==0x00000000
3322 ) //Sometimes this value is wrong, we have to test this
3323 {
3324 //Filling
3325 InfoCodecID_Format_Type=InfoCodecID_Format_Riff;
3326 CodecID.From_CC4(Compression);
3327 if (Compression==0x00000000)
3328 {
3329 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Format, "RGB", Unlimited, true, true);
3330 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Codec, "RGB", Unlimited, true, true); //Raw RGB, not handled by automatic codec mapping
3331 }
3332 else
3333 {
3334 CodecID_Fill(CodecID, Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff);
3335 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Codec, CodecID, true); //FormatTag, may be replaced by codec parser
3336 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Codec_CC, CodecID); //FormatTag
3337 }
3338 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Width, Width, 10, true);
3339 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Height, Height, 10, true);
3340 if (Resolution==32 && Compression==0x74736363) //tscc
3341 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitDepth", 8);
3342 else if (Compression==0x44495633) //DIV3
3343 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitDepth", 8);
3344 else if (Compression==0x44585342) //DXSB
3345 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitDepth", Resolution);
3346 else if (Resolution>16 && MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(StreamKind_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Ztring().From_CC4(Compression), InfoCodecID_ColorSpace).find(__T("RGBA"))!=std::string::npos) //RGB codecs
3347 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitDepth", Resolution/4);
3348 else if (Compression==0x00000000 //RGB
3349 || MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(StreamKind_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Ztring().From_CC4(Compression), InfoCodecID_ColorSpace).find(__T("RGB"))!=std::string::npos) //RGB codecs
3350 {
3351 if (Resolution==32)
3352 {
3353 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Format), "RGBA", Unlimited, true, true);
3354 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitDepth", Resolution/4); //With Alpha
3355 }
3356 else
3357 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitDepth", Resolution<=16?8:(Resolution/3)); //indexed or normal
3358 }
3359 else if (Compression==0x56503632 //VP62
3360 || MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(StreamKind_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Ztring().From_CC4(Compression), InfoCodecID_Format)==__T("H.263") //H.263
3361 || MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(StreamKind_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Ztring().From_CC4(Compression), InfoCodecID_Format)==__T("VC-1")) //VC-1
3362 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitDepth", Resolution/3);
3363 }
3364
3365 //Creating the parser
3366 CodecID_Manage();
3367
3368 FILLING_END();
3369
3370 if (Data_Remain())
3371 {
3372 Element_Begin1("Private data");
3373 if (Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)
3374 {
3375 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_FFV1_YES)
3376 if (Compression==0x46465631) //FFV1
3377 Open_Buffer_OutOfBand(Stream[TrackNumber].Parser);
3378 #endif
3379 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_FFV1_YES)
3380 if (Compression==0x46465648) //FFVH
3381 {
3382 ((File_HuffYuv*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->IsOutOfBandData=true; //TODO: implement ISOutOfBandData in a generic maner
3383 Open_Buffer_Continue(Stream[TrackNumber].Parser);
3384 Element_Offset=Element_Size;
3385 }
3386 #endif
3387 }
3388 else
3389 Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset, "Unknown");
3390 Element_End0();
3391 }
3392}

3559//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
3560void File_Mk::Segment_Tracks_TrackEntry_TrackType()
3561{

3563
3564 //Parsing
3565 int64u UInteger=UInteger_Get();
3566
3567 //Filling
3568 FILLING_BEGIN();
3569 if (Segment_Info_Count>1)
3570 return; //First element has the priority
3571 TrackType=UInteger;
3572 switch(UInteger)
3573 {
3574 case 0x01 :
3575 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Video);
3576 break;
3577 case 0x02 :
3578 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Audio);
3579 break;
3580 case 0x11 :
3581 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Text );
3582 break;
3583 default : ;

3587 {

4184//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
4185void File_Mk::CodecID_Manage()
4186{
4187 if (TrackType==(int64u)-1 || TrackNumber==(int64u)-1 || CodecID.empty() || Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)
4188 return; //Not ready (or not needed)
4189
4190 if (Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_CodecID)).empty())
4191 {
4192 CodecID_Fill(CodecID, StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Matroska);
4193 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Codec), CodecID);
4194 }
4195
4196 //Creating the parser
4197 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_MPEG4V_YES) || defined(MEDIAINFO_AVC_YES) || defined(MEDIAINFO_HEVC_YES) || defined(MEDIAINFO_VC1_YES) || defined(MEDIAINFO_DIRAC_YES) || defined(MEDIAINFO_MPEGV_YES) || defined(MEDIAINFO_VP8_YES) || defined(MEDIAINFO_OGG_YES) || defined(MEDIAINFO_DTS_YES)
4198 const Ztring &Format=MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(StreamKind_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Type, CodecID, InfoCodecID_Format);
4199 #endif
4200 if (0);
4201 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_MPEG4V_YES)
4202 else if (Format==__T("MPEG-4 Visual"))
4203 {
4204 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Mpeg4v;
4205 ((File_Mpeg4v*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->FrameIsAlwaysComplete=true;
4206 }
4207 #endif
4208 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_AVC_YES)
4209 else if (Format==__T("AVC"))
4210 {
4211 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Avc;
4212 ((File_Avc*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->FrameIsAlwaysComplete=true;
4213 if (InfoCodecID_Format_Type==InfoCodecID_Format_Matroska)
4214 {
4215 ((File_Avc*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->MustSynchronize=false;
4216 ((File_Avc*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->MustParse_SPS_PPS=true;
4217 ((File_Avc*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->SizedBlocks=true;
4218 }
4219 }
4220 #endif
4221 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_HEVC_YES)
4222 else if (Format==__T("HEVC"))
4223 {
4224 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Hevc;
4225 ((File_Hevc*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->FrameIsAlwaysComplete=true;
4226 if (InfoCodecID_Format_Type==InfoCodecID_Format_Matroska)
4227 {
4228 ((File_Hevc*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->MustSynchronize=false;
4229 ((File_Hevc*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->MustParse_VPS_SPS_PPS=true;
4230 ((File_Hevc*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->MustParse_VPS_SPS_PPS_FromMatroska=true;
4231 ((File_Hevc*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->SizedBlocks=true;
4232 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
4233 if (Config->Demux_Hevc_Transcode_Iso14496_15_to_AnnexB_Get())
4234 {
4235 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser->Demux_Level=2; //Container
4236 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser->Demux_UnpacketizeContainer=true;
4237 }
4238 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
4239 }
4240 }
4241 #endif
4242 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_FFV1_YES)
4243 else if (Format==__T("FFV1"))
4244 {
4245 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Ffv1;
4246 ((File_Ffv1*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->Width=Retrieve(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Width).To_int32u();
4247 ((File_Ffv1*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->Height=Retrieve(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Height).To_int32u();
4248 }
4249 #endif
4250 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_HUFFYUV_YES)
4251 else if (Format==__T("HuffYUV"))
4252 {
4253 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_HuffYuv;
4254 }
4255 #endif
4256 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_VC1_YES)
4257 else if (Format==__T("VC-1"))
4258 {
4259 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Vc1;
4260 ((File_Vc1*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->FrameIsAlwaysComplete=true;
4261 }
4262 #endif
4263 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_DIRAC_YES)
4264 else if (Format==__T("Dirac"))
4265 {
4266 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Dirac;
4267 }
4268 #endif
4269 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_MPEGV_YES)
4270 else if (Format==__T("MPEG Video"))
4271 {
4272 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Mpegv;
4273 ((File_Mpegv*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->FrameIsAlwaysComplete=true;
4274 }
4275 #endif
4276 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_PRORES_YES)
4277 else if (Format==__T("ProRes"))
4278 {
4279 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_ProRes;
4280 }
4281 #endif
4282 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_VP8_YES)
4283 else if (Format==__T("VP8"))
4284 {
4285 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Vp8;
4286 }
4287 #endif
4288 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_OGG_YES)
4289 else if (Format==__T("Theora") || Format==__T("Vorbis"))
4290 {
4291 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Ogg;
4292 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser->MustSynchronize=false;
4293 ((File_Ogg*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->XiphLacing=true;
4294 }
4295 #endif
4296 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_RM_YES)
4297 else if (CodecID.find(__T("V_REAL/"))==0)
4298 {
4299 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Rm;
4300 ((File_Rm*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->FromMKV_StreamType=Stream_Video;
4301 }
4302 #endif
4303 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_AC3_YES)
4304 else if (Format==__T("AC-3") || Format==__T("E-AC-3") || Format==__T("TrueHD"))
4305 {
4306 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Ac3;
4307 }
4308 #endif
4309 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_DTS_YES)
4310 else if (Format==__T("DTS"))
4311 {
4312 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Dts;
4313 }
4314 #endif
4315 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_AAC_YES)
4316 else if (CodecID==(__T("A_AAC")))
4317 {
4318 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Aac;
4319 ((File_Aac*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->Mode=File_Aac::Mode_AudioSpecificConfig;
4320 }
4321 #endif
4322 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_AAC_YES)
4323 else if (CodecID.find(__T("A_AAC/"))==0)
4324 {
4325 Ztring Profile;
4326 int8u audioObjectType=0, Version=0, SBR=2, PS=2;
4327 if (CodecID==__T("A_AAC/MPEG2/MAIN")) {Version=2; Profile=__T("Main"); audioObjectType=1;}
4328 else if (CodecID==__T("A_AAC/MPEG2/LC")) {Version=2; Profile=__T("LC"); audioObjectType=2; SBR=0;}
4329 else if (CodecID==__T("A_AAC/MPEG2/LC/SBR")) {Version=2; Profile=__T("HE-AAC / LC"); audioObjectType=2; SBR=1;}
4330 else if (CodecID==__T("A_AAC/MPEG2/SSR")) {Version=2; Profile=__T("SSR"); audioObjectType=3;}
4331 else if (CodecID==__T("A_AAC/MPEG4/MAIN")) {Version=4; Profile=__T("Main"); audioObjectType=1;}
4332 else if (CodecID==__T("A_AAC/MPEG4/LC")) {Version=4; Profile=__T("LC"); audioObjectType=2; SBR=0;}
4333 else if (CodecID==__T("A_AAC/MPEG4/LC/SBR")) {Version=4; Profile=__T("HE-AAC / LC"); audioObjectType=2; SBR=1; PS=0;}
4334 else if (CodecID==__T("A_AAC/MPEG4/LC/SBR/PS")){Version=4; Profile=__T("HE-AACv2 / HE-AAC / LC"); audioObjectType=2; SBR=1; PS=1;}
4335 else if (CodecID==__T("A_AAC/MPEG4/SSR")) {Version=4; Profile=__T("SSR"); audioObjectType=3;}
4336 else if (CodecID==__T("A_AAC/MPEG4/LTP")) {Version=4; Profile=__T("LTP"); audioObjectType=4;}
4337 else if (CodecID==__T("raac")) { Profile=__T("LC"); audioObjectType=2;}
4338 else if (CodecID==__T("racp")) { Profile=__T("HE-AAC / LC"); audioObjectType=2; SBR=1; PS=0;}
4339
4340 if (Version>0)
4341 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Format_Version, Version==2?"Version 2":"Version 4");
4342 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Format_Profile, Profile);
4343 if (SBR!=2)
4344 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Format_Settings_SBR, SBR?"Yes":"No");
4345 if (PS!=2)
4346 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Format_Settings_PS, PS?"Yes":"No");
4347 int64s sampling_frequency=Retrieve(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_SamplingRate).To_int64s();
4348
4349 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Aac;
4350 ((File_Aac*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->Mode=File_Aac::Mode_AudioSpecificConfig;
4351 ((File_Aac*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->AudioSpecificConfig_OutOfBand(sampling_frequency, audioObjectType, SBR==1?true:false, PS==1?true:false, SBR==1?true:false, PS==1?true:false);
4352 }
4353 #endif
4354 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_AAC_YES)
4355 else if (Format==(__T("AAC")))
4356 {
4357 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Aac;
4358 ((File_Aac*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->Mode=File_Aac::Mode_ADTS;
4359 }
4360 #endif
4361 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_MPEGA_YES)
4362 else if (Format==__T("MPEG Audio"))
4363 {
4364 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Mpega;
4365 }
4366 #endif
4367 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_FLAC_YES)
4368 else if (Format==__T("Flac"))
4369 {
4370 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Flac;
4371 }
4372 #endif
4373 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_OPUS_YES)
4374 else if (CodecID.find(__T("A_OPUS"))==0) //http://wiki.xiph.org/MatroskaOpus
4375 {
4376 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Opus;
4377 }
4378 #endif
4379 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_WVPK_YES)
4380 else if (Format==__T("WavPack"))
4381 {
4382 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Wvpk;
4383 ((File_Wvpk*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->FromMKV=true;
4384 }
4385 #endif
4386 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_TTA_YES)
4387 else if (Format==__T("TTA"))
4388 {
4389 //Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Tta; //Parser is not needed, because header is useless and dropped (the parser analyses only the header)
4390 }
4391 #endif
4392 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_PCM_YES)
4393 else if (Format==__T("PCM"))
4394 {
4395 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Pcm;
4396 ((File_Pcm*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->Codec=CodecID;
4397 }
4398 #endif
4399 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_RM_YES)
4400 else if (CodecID.find(__T("A_REAL/"))==0)
4401 {
4402 Stream[TrackNumber].Parser=new File_Rm;
4403 ((File_Rm*)Stream[TrackNumber].Parser)->FromMKV_StreamType=Stream_Audio;
4404 }
4405 #endif
4406 Element_Code=TrackNumber;
4407 Open_Buffer_Init(Stream[TrackNumber].Parser);
4408
4409 CodecID.clear();
4410}

4412//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
4413void File_Mk::CodecPrivate_Manage()
4414{
4415 if (CodecPrivate==NULL || TrackNumber==(int64u)-1 || TrackType==(int64u)-1 || Retrieve(Stream[TrackNumber].StreamKind, Stream[TrackNumber].StreamPos, "CodecID").empty())
4416 return; //Not ready (or not needed)
4417
4418 //Codec Private is already here, so we can parse it now
4419 const int8u* Buffer_Save=Buffer;
4420 size_t Buffer_Offset_Save=Buffer_Offset;
4421 size_t Buffer_Size_Save=Buffer_Size;
4422 int64u Element_Size_Save=Element_Size;
4423 Buffer=CodecPrivate;
4424 Buffer_Offset=0;
4425 Buffer_Size=CodecPrivate_Size;
4426 Element_Offset=0;
4427 Element_Size=Buffer_Size;
4428 Segment_Tracks_TrackEntry_CodecPrivate__Parse();
4429 Buffer=Buffer_Save;
4430 Buffer_Offset=Buffer_Offset_Save;
4431 Buffer_Size=Buffer_Size_Save;
4432 Element_Size=Element_Size_Save;
4433 Element_Offset=Element_Size_Save;
4434 delete[] CodecPrivate; CodecPrivate=NULL;
4435 CodecPrivate_Size=0;
4436}

4442//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
4443void File_Mk::JumpTo (int64u GoToValue)
4444{
4445 //Clearing CRC data
4446 for (size_t i = 0; i<CRC32Compute.size(); i++)
4447 if (CRC32Compute[i].UpTo)
4448 {
4449 //Searching and replacing CRC-32 information
4450 //TODO: better implementation without this ugly hack
4451 #if MEDIAINFO_TRACE
4452 element_details::Element_Node *node = Get_Trace_Node(i);
4453 if (node)
4454 {
4455 std::string ToSearchInInfo=std::string("Not tested ")+Ztring::ToZtring(i).To_UTF8()+' '+Ztring::ToZtring(CRC32Compute[i].Expected).To_UTF8();
4456 CRC32_Check_In_Node(ToSearchInInfo, "Not tested", node);
4457 }
4458 #endif //MEDIAINFO_TRACE
4459
4460 CRC32Compute[i].UpTo=0;
4461 }
4462 CRC32Compute.clear();
4463
4464 //GoTo
4465 GoTo(GoToValue);
4466}

4468//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
4469//We want to parse more than the 1st element only if one of the following:
4470//-trace is activated
4471//-request for parsing all and CRC-32 is present
4472//TODO: if trace is not activated and CRC-32 is present, we don't need to parse all elements, we only need to do the CRC-32 check
4473void File_Mk::TestMultipleInstances (size_t* Instances)
4474{
4475 #if MEDIAINFO_TRACE
4476 bool ParseAll=false;
4477 if (Trace_Activated)
4478 ParseAll=true;
4479 #else //MEDIAINFO_TRACE
4480 static bool ParseAll = false;
4481 #endif //MEDIAINFO_TRACE
4482 if (!ParseAll && Config->ParseSpeed >= 1.0)
4483 {
4484 //Probing, checking if CRC-32 is present
4485 if (Element_Size < 1)
4486 {
4487 Element_WaitForMoreData();
4488 return;
4489 }
4490 #if MEDIAINFO_TRACE
4491 if (Buffer[Buffer_Offset] == 0xBF) //CRC-32 element
4492 ParseAll=true;
4493 #endif //MEDIAINFO_TRACE
4494 }
4495
4496 if ((!Instances || *Instances) && !ParseAll)
4497 Skip_XX(Element_TotalSize_Get(), "No need, skipping");
4498
4499 if (Instances)
4500 (*Instances)++;
4501}

4504#if MEDIAINFO_TRACE
4505bool File_Mk::CRC32_Check_In_Node(const std::string& ToSearchInInfo, const std::string& info, element_details::Element_Node *node)
4506{
4507 //Check in the current node
4508 for (size_t i = 0; i < node->Infos.size(); ++i)
4509 {
4510 if (node->Infos[i]->data == ToSearchInInfo)
4511 {
4512 node->Infos[i]->data = info;
4513 return true;
4514 }
4515 }
4516
4517 //Check in the children of the current node
4518 for (size_t i = 0; i < node->Children.size(); ++i)
4519 {
4520 if (CRC32_Check_In_Node(ToSearchInInfo, info, node->Children[i]))
4521 return true;
4522 }
4523
4524 return false;
4525}

4528//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
4529void File_Mk::CRC32_Check ()
4530{
4531 for (size_t i = 0; i<CRC32Compute.size(); i++)
4532 if (CRC32Compute[i].UpTo && File_Offset + Buffer_Offset - (size_t)Header_Size >= CRC32Compute[i].From)
4533 {
4534 CRC32_Compute(CRC32Compute[i].Computed, Buffer + Buffer_Offset - (size_t)Header_Size, Buffer + Buffer_Offset + (size_t)(Element_WantNextLevel?Element_Offset:Element_Size));
4535 if (File_Offset + Buffer_Offset + (Element_WantNextLevel?Element_Offset:Element_Size) >= CRC32Compute[i].UpTo)
4536 {
4537 CRC32Compute[i].Computed ^= 0xFFFFFFFF;
4538
4539 #if MEDIAINFO_TRACE
4540 if (Trace_Activated)
4541 {
4542 //Searching and replacing CRC-32 information
4543 //TODO: better implementation without this ugly hack
4544
4545 element_details::Element_Node *node = Get_Trace_Node(i);
4546 if (node)
4547 {
4548 std::string ToSearchInInfo=std::string("Not tested ")+Ztring::ToZtring(i).To_UTF8()+' '+Ztring::ToZtring(CRC32Compute[i].Expected).To_UTF8();
4549 CRC32_Check_In_Node(ToSearchInInfo, CRC32Compute[i].Computed == CRC32Compute[i].Expected?"OK":"NOK", node);
4550 }
4551
4552 //Debug
4553 //size_t Element_Level_Save=Element_Level;
4554 //Element_Level=i;
4555 //Element_Info(CRC32Compute[i].Computed == CRC32Compute[i].Expected ? __T("CRC32 check OK"):__T("CRC32 check NOK"));
4556 //Element_Level=Element_Level_Save;
4557 }
4558 #endif //MEDIAINFO_TRACE
4559
4560 if (CRC32Compute[i].Computed != CRC32Compute[i].Expected)
4561 {
4562 Fill(Stream_General, 0, "CRC_Error_Pos", CRC32Compute[i].Pos);
4563 }
4564
4565 CRC32Compute[i].UpTo=0;
4566 }
4567 }
4568}

4570//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
4571void File_Mk::CRC32_Compute(int32u &CRC32, int32u Init, const int8u* Buffer_Current, const int8u* Buffer_End)
4572{
4573 CRC32 ^= Init;
4574
4575 CRC32_Compute(CRC32, Buffer_Current, Buffer_End);
4576
4577 CRC32 ^= Init;
4578}
4579
4580//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
4581void File_Mk::CRC32_Compute(int32u &CRC32, const int8u* Buffer_Current, const int8u* Buffer_End)
4582{
4583 while(Buffer_Current<Buffer_End)
4584 CRC32=(CRC32>>8) ^ Mk_CRC32_Table[(CRC32&0xFF)^*Buffer_Current++];
4585}
